<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Rare, known so far from Jabal Fayfa, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" unit="km" value="80.0">80 km</quantity>
<collectionCode country="Australia" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14575" name="University of New England" type="Herbarium">NE</collectionCode>
<collectingRegion country="Saudi Arabia" name="Jizan">Jazan</collectingRegion>
, SW of the country (
<bibRefCitation author="Plowes, DCH" journalOrPublisher="Asklepios" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="3 - 15" refId="B35" refString="Plowes, DCH, 2012. New taxa in the Huernia saudi-arabica complex. Asklepios 114: 3 - 15" title="New taxa in the Huernia saudi-arabica complex." volume="114" year="2012">Plowes 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">General distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Probably endemic to SW Arabian Peninsula known so far from 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Habitat and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Occurs in granitic outcrops at 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" unit="m" value="1550.0">1550 m</quantity>
alt (
<bibRefCitation author="Collenette, S" journalOrPublisher="National Commission for Wildlife Conservation and Development, Riyadh" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" refId="B15" refString="Collenette, S, 1999. Wildflowers of Saudi Arabia. National Commission for Wildlife Conservation and Development, Riyadh" title="Wildflowers of Saudi Arabia." year="1999">Collenette 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Clearly distinct by its campanulate corolla that is dotted with maroon inside and has a very foetid odour when it opens.</paragraph>
