<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Foetidus (Latin) smelly, for the strong, unpleasant smell of flowers.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alharbi &amp; Al-Qthanin" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Alharbi &amp; Al-Qthanin" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceropegia lodarensis subsp. var. var. foetida" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lodarensis" subSpecies="var." variety="foetida">Ceropegia lodarensis var. foetida</taxonomicName>
is estimated to have an EOO of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0173" unit="km" value="80.173">80.173 km</quantity>
2 (which would place the species in Critically Endangered, 
<collectionCode country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
) and AOO of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" unit="km" value="88.0">88 km</quantity>
2 (which would place it in 
<collectionCode>EN</collectionCode>
). The size of its populations and current threats are not well-known, but populations in mountainous areas in 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
are likely impacted by agriculture, overgrazing, development and tourism. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alharbi &amp; Al-Qthanin" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Alharbi &amp; Al-Qthanin" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceropegia lodarensis subsp. var. var. foetida" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lodarensis" subSpecies="var." variety="foetida">Ceropegia lodarensis var. foetida</taxonomicName>
should be considered Data Deficient (
<collectionCode country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13033" name="Forest Research Institute, Indian Council of Forestry Research and Education" type="Herbarium">DD</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
